shapes:RolebasedRequestTemplateShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass ids:RolebasedRequest ;
    sh:node shapes:HasProviderOrConsumerNodeShape ;
    sh:property shapes:RolebasedRequestTemplate-permissionPropertyShape ;
    sh:message "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/RolebasedRequestTemplates/RolebasedRequestTemplateShape.ttl> (RolebasedRequestTemplateShape): In a _:RolebasedRequest a) the ids:provider property must point to one participant or b) the ids:consumer property must point to one participant or c) the ids:provider and the ids:consumer must point to one participant. This can in any case be a) an IRI or b) an ids:Participant. The ids:permission property must point to at exactly one ids:Permission. In the ids:Permission the ids:target and ids:action properties and at least one of (ids:assigner or ids:assignee) pointing to a participant have to be specified. There must be two ids:constraint properties pointing to an ids:Constraint each. Within one ids:Constraint the ids:leftOperand must point to idsc:USER, the ids:operator must point to idsc:MEMBER_OF, the ids:rightOperandReference must specify the URI of the participant organization as an IRI and the ids:pipEndpoint must point to a PipUri. Within the other ids:Constraint the ids:leftOperand must point to idsc:USER, the ids:operator must point to idsc:HAS_MEMBERSHIP, the ids:rightOperandReference must specify the URI of the participant's role as an IRI and the ids:pipEndpoint must point to a PipUri."@en ;
.


shapes:RolebasedRequestTemplate-permissionPropertyShape
    a sh:PropertyShape ;
    sh:path ids:permission ;
    sh:class ids:Permission ;
    sh:node shapes:RolebasedRequestPermissionTemplateShape ;
    sh:minCount 1 ;
    sh:maxCount 1 ;
    sh:severity sh:Violation ;
    sh:message "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/RolebasedRequestTemplates/RolebasedRequestTemplateShape.ttl> (RolebasedRequestTemplateShape-permissionPropertyShape): In a _:RolebasedRequest the ids:permission property must point to at exactly one ids:Permission. In the ids:Permission the ids:target and ids:action properties and at least one of (ids:assigner or ids:assignee) pointing to a participant have to be specified. There must be two ids:constraint properties pointing to an ids:Constraint each. Within one ids:Constraint the ids:leftOperand must point to idsc:USER, the ids:operator must point to idsc:MEMBER_OF, the ids:rightOperandReference must specify the URI of the participant organization as an IRI and the ids:pipEndpoint must point to a PipUri. Within the other ids:Constraint the ids:leftOperand must point to idsc:USER, the ids:operator must point to idsc:HAS_MEMBERSHIP, the ids:rightOperandReference must specify the URI of the participant's role as an IRI and the ids:pipEndpoint must point to a PipUri."@en ;
.


shapes:RolebasedRequestPermissionTemplateShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:node shapes:HasAssignerOrAssigneeNodeShape ;
    sh:property shapes:PermissionTemplate-targetPropertyShape ;
    sh:property shapes:PermissionTemplate-actionPropertyShape ;
    sh:property shapes:RolebasedPermissionTemplate-constraintPropertyShape ;
    sh:property shapes:RolebasedPermissionTemplate-constraintPropertyForMemberShape ;
    sh:property shapes:RolebasedPermissionTemplate-constraintPropertyForMembershipShape ;
.
